Rating: 0
I have just started to cook more fish, and this recipe is one that has been added to our regular rotation. Very light and flavorful. I vary it depending on what's on hand, and have used Panko bread crumbs and varied the herbs. To save time, I also oven fry instead of pan fry, by drizzling olive oil over breaded fillets and baking in 500 degree oven for about 7 or 8 minutes.

