I don't know what that other bloke did wrong, but I thought this was an amazing recipe. I had no problems with it at all. My boyfriend is not a fan of fish, and he loved it. I did find that the bread crumbs got clumpy as I coated the fish, so the last fillet was much more difficult to coat, but that's easily remedied by reserving half the crumbs and coating them in two batches. Such an easy recipe, and wonderful results.

