Rating: 4
This recipe is absolutely fantastic! I've used it for both sole and flounder with absolutely amazing, flavorful results. Even my bosses (I'm a nanny) liked it (the boy loved it, too, but he's not very picky). Marinating it longer (about an hour) seems to make it even better. I recommend fresh, curly parsley instead of the lighter tasting flat parsley. A definite regular addition. Serve it with mesclun salad and baguette slices.

