Rating: 4
This was incredible! My only changes were using 2% rather than whole milk (what I had on hand) and dry vermouth instead of white wine, because I didn't have an open bottle. Rather than keeping the fish warm in the oven, I just used two skillets and fried the fish simultaneously. My husband and I both loved the contrast of the crispy buttery breading and the moist, flaky fish inside. I served this with roasted baby potatoes with garlic, and blanched green beans with sour cream and thyme dressing. Fabulous and easy weeknight meal, but it was so good I'm definintely serving it to guests as well.

Rating: 4
